This system knowledge is intented to be modified for the Teton Geographic Area in Wyoming. This is only a starting point for development of this geographic area.
This initial default knowldge is from modification of the Eastside of Region One Geographic Area by Ecosystem Research Group of Missoula for work on the Shoshone National Forest.
Default logic and probability values developed through a series of workshops with silviculturists, ecologists, planners, and resource specialists for the "Analysis of the Management Situation - Eastside Planning Zone", October 199 through March 2000. The logic and values were tested on a sample landscape for each Forest in the Planning Zone.
Mountain PIne Beetle in Lodgepole Pine: The logic for mountain pine beetle probability in lodgepole pine is built upon the hazard rating system in General Technical Report INT-36, "Guidelines for reducing losses of lodgepole pine to the mountain pine beetle in unmanaged stands in the Rocky Mountains, Amman et. al. 1977
Mountain Pine Beetle in Ponderosa Pine: The basis for the probability starts with the determination of a hazard. This hazard is based on the research work documented in "Risk Rating Guide for Mountain Pine Beetle in Black Hills Ponderosa Pine" Stevens, McCambridge, and Edminster 1980
